<p dir="auto"><a href="https://github.com/csstools/postcss-plugins/tree/main/plugins/postcss-nesting">PostCSS Nesting</a> lets you nest style rules inside each other, following the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-nesting-1/" rel="nofollow">CSS Nesting specification</a>.</p>
<p dir="auto">If you want nested rules the same way <a href="https://sass-lang.com/" rel="nofollow">Sass</a> works
you might want to use <a href="https://github.com/postcss/postcss-nested">PostCSS Nested</a> instead.</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-postcss notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=".foo {
	color: red;

	&amp;:hover {
		color: green;
	}

	&gt; .bar {
		color: blue;
	}

	@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
		color: cyan;
	}
}

/* becomes */

.foo {
	color: red;
}
.foo:hover {
		color: green;
	}
.foo &gt; .bar {
		color: blue;
	}
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
	.foo {
		color: cyan;
}
	}"><pre><span class="pl-e">.foo</span> {
	<span class="pl-c1">color</span>: red;

	<span class="pl-ent">&amp;<span class="pl-e">:hover</span></span> {
		<span class="pl-c1">color</span>: green;
	}

	<span class="pl-k">&gt;</span> <span class="pl-e">.bar</span> {
		<span class="pl-c1">color</span>: blue;
	}

	<span class="pl-k">@media </span>(<span class="pl-c1">prefers-color-scheme</span>: dark) {
		<span class="pl-c1">color</span>: cyan;
	}
}

<span class="pl-c">/* becomes */</span>

<span class="pl-e">.foo</span> {
	<span class="pl-c1">color</span>: red;
}
<span class="pl-e">.foo<span class="pl-e">:hover</span></span> {
		<span class="pl-c1">color</span>: green;
	}
<span class="pl-e">.foo</span> <span class="pl-k">&gt;</span> <span class="pl-e">.bar</span> {
		<span class="pl-c1">color</span>: blue;
	}
<span class="pl-k">@media </span>(<span class="pl-c1">prefers-color-scheme</span>: dark) {
	<span class="pl-e">.foo</span> {
		<span class="pl-c1">color</span>: cyan;
}
	}</pre></div>
