<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto"><g-emoji class="g-emoji" alias="warning">⚠️</g-emoji> <code>@nest</code> has been removed from the specification.</h2><a id="user-content-️-nest-has-been-removed-from-the-specification" class="anchor-element" aria-label="Permalink: ⚠️ @nest has been removed from the specification." href="#️-nest-has-been-removed-from-the-specification"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">Previous iterations of the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-nesting-1/" rel="nofollow">CSS Nesting specification</a> required using <code>@nest</code> for certain selectors.</p>
<p dir="auto"><code>@nest</code> was removed from the specification completely.
Future versions of this plugin will error if you use <code>@nest</code>.</p>
<p dir="auto">We advice everyone to migrate their codebase <strong>now</strong> to nested CSS without <code>@nest</code>.<br>
We published a <a href="https://github.com/csstools/postcss-plugins/tree/main/plugins-stylelint/no-at-nest-rule#csstoolsstylelint-no-at-nest-rule">Stylelint Plugin</a> to help you migrate.</p>
<p dir="auto">example warning:</p>
<blockquote>
<p dir="auto"><code>@nest</code> was removed from the CSS Nesting specification and will be removed from PostCSS Nesting in the next major version.
Change <code>@nest foo &amp; {}</code> to <code>foo &amp; {}</code> to migrate to the latest standard.</p>
</blockquote>
<p dir="auto">You can silence this warning with a new <code>silenceAtNestWarning</code> plugin option.</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-js notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="postcssNesting({
	silenceAtNestWarning: true
})"><pre><span class="pl-en">postcssNesting</span><span class="pl-kos">(</span><span class="pl-kos">{</span>
	<span class="pl-c1">silenceAtNestWarning</span>: <span class="pl-c1">true</span>
<span class="pl-kos">}</span><span class="pl-kos">)</span></pre></div>
